Visceral photophore rounded, divided medially by septum that is joined to ventral mantle, ventral to ink sac and dorsal to, and associated with, anus (
Figure 8g
). Paired openings slitlike, teardrop-shaped, without protruding pores. Both sexes with large pads of glandular tissue on each side of mantle cavity between gills and funnel organ.

Arms 1 of males hectocotylised with swollen and glandular ventral margins. Hectocotylus suckers uniform in size, sometimes crowded into three series. Remaining arm suckers biserial. Males with enlarged suckers midway along arms 2 (
Figure 9a
). Females with enlarged suckers on distal end of arms 2.

Chitinous arm sucker rims: infundibulum with 3–4 rows of pavement-like processes (
Figure 9b–d
), peripheral sucker rim processes small, tightly packed, rest irregular oval. Chitinous inner ring of normal arm suckers with teeth on one side only in males, very slightly crenulated on opposite side (
Figure 9b, c
). Sucker rings smooth in females.

Tentacles slender, stalks naked, semicircular in cross section. Club relatively short; ClLI males 19.7– 25.0 –35.5 (SD, 5.8), females 32.6– 38.7 –44.8 (SD, 8.6), straight, tapers to rounded end distally; sucker-bearing face curved ( Figure 9e, f ). Suckers approximately 0.5–1.5 mm in diameter in centre of club. ClRC 10–17 (usually 15); suckers enlarged slightly at base of club. Aboral keel absent; tentacle organ extends from proximal end of sucker-bearing portion of club, along tentacle stalk well beyond club sucker-bearing portion ( Figure 9e ); shallow median groove extends along length of club. Club sucker dentition (
Figure 9g , h
): inner ring without teeth, and bearing ring of widely-spaced pegs; infundibulum with three rows of pavement-like processes; inner two rows hexagonal or pentagonal basally; pegs narrower than bases of processes; outer row wedge-shaped without pegs (
Figure 9g
); pegs with regular pitted surfaces ( Figure 9h ).

Upper beak (
Figure 10a
) with pointed rostrum, hood convex, high above crest posteriorly; jaw curved, not sharply angled. Lower beak (
Figure 10b
) with pointed, short rostrum, rostral edge obtuse, curved; hood notch absent, wings straight. Distinct dark pigmentation restricted to rostrum and hood.

Radula with seven series of teeth (
Figure 10c
). Rhachidian simple, without cusps, triangular, sides straight, with narrow bases. First lateral teeth with pointed cusps, strongly displaced laterally, directed towards midline of radula. Second and third laterals, curved. Third laterals scythe-like, longer than second lateral teeth.
